5.05
                       
Expiration of Claims
.
 
(a)
                                
Except for Losses due to fraud of the Company or a Seller or as set forth in the second sentence of this , the ability of the Buyer Indemnitees to receive indemnification under or proceeds from the Escrow Account pursuant to for any Loss shall terminate on the applicable Survival Date (which (i) in respect of Losses under , or shall be the first anniversary of the Closing Date, (ii) in respect of Seller Taxes shall be the eighteen month anniversary of the Closing Date; and (iii) in respect of Losses under or shall be the date of payment of all amounts due pursuant to the final resolution of the matters set forth on with the Internal Revenue Service and any state taxing authorities), unless the Buyer Indemnitees shall have incurred a Loss (with respect to any claim that has been made) and (except as provided in ) made either a written claim for indemnification pursuant to or a written claim for receipt of proceeds from the Escrow Account pursuant to , as applicable, on or prior to the applicable Survival Date.  Notwithstanding the foregoing, the ability of the Buyer Indemnitees to receive indemnification under for any Loss in respect of a breach or inaccuracy of the representations and warranties in shall terminate on the fourth anniversary of the Closing Date, unless the Buyer Indemnitees shall have incurred a Loss (with respect to any claim that has been made) and made a written claim for indemnification pursuant to on or prior to the fourth anniversary of the Closing Date.  If Buyer Indemnitees have made either a written claim for indemnification pursuant to , a written claim for receipt of proceeds from the Escrow Account pursuant to or are deemed to have made a written claim pursuant to , as applicable, on or prior to the applicable Survival Date, such claim, if then unresolved, shall not be extinguished by the passage of the applicable Survival Date.
