"LIBO Rate"
For any Interest Period with respect to a LIBO Loan, the rate per annum determined on the basis of (i) the offered rate for deposits in U.S. dollars of amounts equal or comparable to the principal amount of such Loan offered for a term comparable to such Interest Period, which rates appear on the Reuters Screen LIBOR01 Page (or any successor page) effective as of 11:00 A.M., London time, two Business Days prior to the first day of such Interest Period (the ) or if such rate is unavailable, the rate (rounded upwards, if necessary, to the nearest 1/100th of one percent) based on the rates at which deposits in U.S. dollars for one month are displayed on page  of the Reuters Screen as of 11:00 a.m. (London time) on the Rate Setting Day (it being understood that if at least two (2) such rates appear on such page, the rate will be the arithmetic mean of such displayed rates), that if no such offered rates appear on such pages, the LIBO Rate for such Interest Period will be the arithmetic average (rounded upwards, if necessary, to the next higher 1/100th of 1%) of rates quoted by not less than two major banks in New York, New York, selected by the Agent, at approximately 10:00 a.m. (Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania time), two Business Days prior to the first day of such Interest Period, for deposits in U.S. dollars offered by
