"Loss Horizon Ratio"
As of any Cut-Off Date, the ratio (expressed as a decimal) computed by dividing (a) the aggregate Credit Sales for the four (4) most recent Calculation Periods (including the Calculation Period ending on such Cut-Off Date), by (b) the Net Pool Balance as of such Cut-Off Date.
 
"Loss Reserve"
For any Calculation Period, the product (expressed as a percentage) of (i) the Stress Factor, times (ii) the highest three-month rolling average Default Ratio during the 12 Calculation Periods ending on the immediately preceding Cut-Off Date, times (iii) the Loss Horizon Ratio as of the immediately preceding Cut-Off Date.
 
